 Earth Planet. Sci. Lett. 17: 120-128) which may be a\nresult of their stay on the surface of an early differentiated asteroid parent\nbody having melted interiors and a strong magnetic field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Nov 2012 16:31:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-11-14"}
